 Reference Number: GAS0047 Job Description: Intended to support continued improvements in scientific rigor and workforce efficiency within the rehabilitation department. The successful candidate will play an integral role in design and implementation of scientific field trials and studies, including monitoring of rehabilitated and managed natural lands within the mining concession. Additional responsibilities include geodata management and cartographic production using ESRI ArcMap, tracking and reporting rehabilitation progress, identifying and implementing opportunities for improved workforce efficiency, and staff mentorship. Staff upskilling and workforce efficiency are integral accountabilities; improvements in these areas will serve as key performance indicators. Responsibilities: Occupational Health and Safety Environmental Staff Mentorship GIS and GPS Support Study Design and Oversight Productivity Management Requirements:Â Qualification and Skill Benefits and Contractual information: